		<p>Pure Unadulterated Bullsh*t. </p>
<p>Not saying smoking is good, humans were not designed to inhale partially incinerated organic materials. As a result smoking anything is not necessarily good for us. </p>
<p>This does not mean that cannabis is unhealthy. I have a question for you though&#8230; if we were not meant to use cannabis as a medicine why do we have receptors that process and accept it and in a related way why is it that even people who have never used cannabis have it in their bodies?</p>
<p> At 15, I took drivers education in high school. Smoked weed every morning before said class. Learned to drive high, took my drivers written, and road test high, I passed both.</p>
<p>I did leave high school without finishing&#8230; got high for 6 months and without opening a textbook for all that time, took six hours of tests in one sitting to pass my GED&#8230; a year ahead of my class.</p>
<p>I have had many jobs including professional truck driver&#8230; you guessed it, did that high also. I have even run carnival rides, thousands of people on a daily basis came to ride my rides&#8230; yep, high all the time.</p>
<p>I have never caused an accident, never caused anyone to get injured, and never injured myself while high. </p>
<p>The odd thing is&#8230; most of the people my age have a medicine cabinet full of medications from the &#8220;doctor&#8221;. I have none&#8230; no pain pills, no appetite suppressors or enhancers, no diabetic meds (everyone in my family is diabetic), no heart meds or blood thinners (plenty of heart attacks in my family), no antidepressants, nothing to help me sleep, and nothing to wake me up&#8230; </p>
<p>Cannabis does it all and more, and that my friends is why it is not approved by the FDA, it does work. I only wish that I had been able to get some into my father before he died of leukemia, I believe it would have done better than that deadly chemo crap.</p>
<p>Been openly using cannabis for 48 years and I ain&#8217;t dead, or thinking impaired yet&#8230;</p>
<p>Just Sayin&#8217; </p>
		
		
