		<p>Although I had an issue with a lot of the claims made in this article, I would like to comment on two in particular.</p>
<p>&#8220;In fact, children and teens are six times likelier to be in treatment for marijuana than for all other illegal drugs combined.&#8221; -Marijuana is illegal and therefore many people choose treatment rather than face harsher persecution when caught. This does not mean anything in regards to its dependency.</p>
<p>&#8220;Marijuana is the most prevalent illegal drug detected in impaired drivers, fatally injured drivers, and motor vehicle crash victims.&#8221; -THC stays in the body far longer than other substances. Therefore, If someone consumes the drug on the 1st of the month and crashes on the 15th, it will still be in their system regardless of if or not they have smoked the past two weeks.</p>
		
		
