		<p>This article is a good example of how our government determines the outcome it wants and then lies to us distorting the existing facts to support their decision to prohibit pot.  From the way that they present their argument it is clear that there will NEVER be enough evidence for them to support ending the prohibition on marijuana.  Because they control the supply of marijuana that can be used for research they can be sure that it is not of the medicinal quality that is available in those states that permit medical marijuana.  Because it requires the approval of the FDA, the DEA, and NIDA to do research on marijuana they can tie any proposed research up for years to obtain approval by creating a bureaucratic nightmare.  Because they will not permit research into the positive benefits of the cannabis plant they believe that only problems will be apparent to bolster their argument.  They are trying to make a plant fit the mold that was made for the approval of chemicals to treat diseases.  Although everyone knows that an apple a day will keep the doctor away these disingenuous SOB&#8217;s are also aware that apples would never meet the criteria for a drug and also could not be given approval to treat any type of illness.  Their system looks out for those in the pharmaceutical industry to make sure that plants with true medicinal benefit are not available to sick folk.  Between 1850 and 1900 about half the prescriptions written by doctors for their patients contained cannabis.  Instead they support the use of a wide variety of drugs that receive rapid approval that are frequently found later to have dangerous side effects to those who use them.  While they keep us busy arguing over the existing evidence they continue to lock up minorities at rates almost four times that are apparent for Caucasians.  The facts also indicate that this plant has never killed by overdose and to protect us from this plant the prohibitionists have locked up over 20 million of our fellow citizens.  The US has 5% of the world&#8217;s population and 25% of the world&#8217;s prisoners largely due to this war on cannabis.  We cannot afford to call ourselves a free country and to continue this madness.  We can either have a free country or we can have a drug free country.  Which do you choose?</p>
		
		
