		<p>This misinformation in the media is called &#8216;Yellow Journalism&#8217; and was around in the 20&#8242;s when Cannabis (Hemp) was called &#8220;Marijuana&#8221; the &#8216;devils weed&#8217; to scare people. This like many things are not for children. Unless the doctor and parents agree that this is the best treatment for the child. But just to get high no I would say its safer then Alcohol but under age people do not need either, its for adults. The problem with prohibition is that it makes it easier for kids to buy then if it was legal and regulated. In my state you have to show proof of age to buy tobacco and alcohol. This why we need it legal to get it out of the hands of dealers and into shops like alcohol.</p>
		
		
