<p>&#8220;There is a direct correlation between “medical” marijuana and decreases in perception of harm and social disapproval.&#8221;</p>
<p>When people learn how great this plant is medically then the false perception of harm is decreased. The claim that more kids use in states that have medical is not true. Dispensaries do not provide to under age people. If there are dispensaries and adults can get cards then there could be less dealers and that would make harder for kids to buy. Less under age use not more.</p>
		
		
