	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-22647">
	<div id="comment-22647">

		<div class="comment-author vcard">
		<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/1c50620f8406efeb882b29d7906d7018?s=52&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cannabisnews.org%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2Fcomfy%2Fstyles%2Fdefault%2Fimg%2Fdefault_avatar.png%3Fs%3D52&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-52 photo' height='52' width='52' />		<cite class="fn">cannabis leo</cite>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
		<a href="http://www.cannabisnews.org/pot-more-dangerous-than-you-know/2013/06/18/#comment-22647">Posted on March 1, 2014 at 1:54 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Welcome to 1930 Pat Prendergast…you&#8217;ll get to this century eventually.  Unlike yourself, I will not disgrace this space with lies and prejudices, fueled by an agenda of hatred.</p>
<p>I was in Glacier Park October 2013 taking pics of wildlife.  I took a side trip to Canada and saw nothing but mountains and wilderness for 30 miles.  On my way back to base camp, I was about 13 miles away from any civilization.  It was 4 pm which meant sunset in an hour or so.  I was in the middle of bear country with no weapon.  I didn&#8217;t realize the risk of getting a flat on the sharp rocks on those mountain roads but I sure learned it quickly.  One of them slashed my right rear tire on the rental suv I was driving.  I pulled over and KNEW I was screwed.  I&#8217;m a very good photographer and a very very poor mechanic.  I hadn&#8217;t a clue how to get the spare tire accessed let alone get the existing tire off.  It would be dark in an hour and I&#8217;d either be freezing in the vehicle or walking with 15 pounds of camera gear through the dark mountains.  There was no cell service in the mountains.  Man was I in a fix.  Right about that time, I saw a vehicle coming around the bend.  I was a bit surprised because I had literally not seen another vehicle for over 2 hours.  It was a red, old beat up toyota pickup truck.  I just stood by my rental and kinda glanced at the guy as he approached.  There was plenty of room for him to pass and I made no effort whatsoever to signal him or indicate I was in a fix.  Still, he slowed and then stopped and asked me if I needed any help.  I admitted what I&#8217;d gotten myself into.  That guy got out of his truck, found a way to get the spare off, changed the tire and put the gear away.  I was floored!  His name is Bobby.  I gave him my business card and told him to contact me down the road.  I&#8217;d still like to do something for the guy.  He told me he was on his way to town to use his cell service to talk with a guy about work the next day.  He&#8217;d been in Montana all his life and was not surprised to see me there with a flat.  He said it happens all the time and Montanans look out for each other.  THAT is freedom brother!! This guy is not sitting around asking for anything &#8211; he is going out and getting it because he believes in his freedom.  Bobby probably saved my life and he would not take a nickel in gratitude from me. I finally insisted he take a $20 bill or I&#8217;d just tear it up for the universe.  He laughed and took it.  And knowing the vibe was there, I asked him if he had a little weed I could buy.  He was probably 10 years my junior, 42 years old or so.  My brothers and sisters reading this know what I mean by the &#8220;vibe&#8221;.  It is the very thing the government is trying to prevent from spreading.  That connection, fueled by truth, insight and righteousness.  It&#8217;s universal.  So Bobby kinda got nervous but he quickly realized I was cool &#8211; here we were in the middle of nowhere and I was from a state on the east coast.  So he gave me what amounted to enough for the next 4 days and would not take a cent for that either.  It made that photo trip that much better.  I pass along this story because things like this have happened to me all over the United States and other parts of the world.  Bobby is a good, decent, hard working American citizen, trying to make his life a good one.  He&#8217;s not harming anyone with his use and he sure as hell SAVED me.  We are all connected and cannabis is the link.  The endocannabinoid system is in its infancy regarding the discovery, which is around the 1980&#8242;s.  We should be thrilled with this miraculous discovery but instead the government squelches any scientific research.  WTF?!!  One of the effects is good weed makes us ponder the truth and what is right and the greedy bastards in charge know that.  We see their greed and corruption even more clearly.  Why is there a need for even one more seconds delay in taking marijuana off Schedule I?  There is no justifiable cause and it disgusts me.  </p>
<p>I am in this fight to win it.  I delivered a persuasive speech advocating the legalization of marijuana while in college in 1982.  I have stood by and watched the lies for 37 years.  No more.  I will be heard and I will not back down.  Are you with me?</p>
		
		
		<div class="reply">
		<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/pot-more-dangerous-than-you-know/2013/06/18/?replytocom=22647#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-22647", "22647", "respond", "938")'>Reply</a>		</div>

